Reasoning: 
1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses the behavior and performance of adaptive optimization methods in machine learning, which is the main focus of this sub-category. 
2. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper investigates the numerical time convergence of the forward Euler approximation of the differential system, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper derives a non-autonomous system of differential equations and studies its trajectories, which is relevant to this sub-category. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the convergence of the differential system to a critical point and conditions for avoiding saddle points and local maxima, which are topics related to this sub-category. 
5. cs.Optimization: The paper studies the differential system as a tool for optimization and introduces a suitable Lyapunov functional to study its rate of convergence, which is the main focus of this sub-category.
